The paper deals with managing intelligence through clustering, ranking, and classification, which are all techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also deals with issues of inconsistency and uncertainty, which are common in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in the sense that it deals with processing and organizing large amounts of data. Finally, the paper involves machine learning (cs.LG) in the sense that it uses clustering and classification algorithms to process the data.
